[2025-08-17 23:13:58][DEBUG][root] Chapter 'In his teenage years, he was always a bit of an isolated child. He was perhaps always a bit of an oddball, as he just liked to watch more than participate. But that all began to change one day when he went to the bookstore with his father and found a book on physiology and medicine.' length: 740 characters, 139 words
