[2025-08-17 23:15:11][DEBUG][root] Chapter 'Losing a patient, on the other hand, was the worst feeling. To desperately try and nurture the spark, only for it to lose its glow anyway. He knew once the spark completely disappeared, there was no way back—no resuscitation possible, no hope for life to return. This was the saddest feeling he could imagine, and the first few deaths took their toll.' length: 2837 characters, 520 words
